HEADWORD: Peachblow
<hw>Peach"blow`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Ceramics)</fld> <def>Of the
delicate purplish pink color likened to that of peach blooms; -- applied
esp. to a Chinese porcelain, small specimens of which bring great prices
in the Western countries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peach-colored</ent>⟦br⟧
